article.description: Montague's late 3-pointers helps Yale beat Penn 55-50
article.headline: Montague's late 3-pointers helps Yale beat Penn 55-50
article.linkText: Montague's late 3-pointers helps Yale beat Penn 55-50
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Jack Montague hit two late 3-pointers and finished with 11 points to cap Yale's come-from-behind, 55-50 victory over Pennsylvania on Saturday night. Yale (21-8, 10-2 Ivy League) keeps pace with Harvard (20-6, 10-2), which beat Columbia on Saturday, for the top spot in the league standings. Yale travels to Harvard on Friday night. Penn (7-18, 2-9) led the entire way until Montague made a 3 and Javier Duren a pair of free throws to give Yale a 48-47 lead with 2:19 to play. Montague added another trey and Justin Sears converted a three-point play to make it 54-47 with :33 left. Penn's Tony Hicks answered with a 3-pointer, but the Quakers missed their last five shots to end it. Javier Duren scored 19 points, including 9-of-10 shooting from the line, to lead Yale. Antonio Woods scored 14 points and dished out six assists for Penn.
